A man was shot and killed by the motorist he tried to rob during peak-hour traffic in Pinetown‚ west of Durban‚ on Monday. Police spokesman Thulani Zwane said a motorist had been sitting in his car in Anderson Road when he was accosted by two men. “It is alleged that one [of the men] switched off the engine and the other put a knife against the neck of the driver‚ before demanding money and his cellphone‚” he said. “The driver pulled out a firearm and fired two shots at the suspects. One died a few metres away from the scene. One was also wounded‚ but ran away. Police are still looking for him‚” said Zwane.